(16333, '94B392C6-540D-46DD-95F8-562146EAF90A', 'This is hard and I‚Äôm sorry you are feeling raw and worn down, love.  I‚Äôve been trying to be better at acknowledging you and your wins. I shared last night a few times how you are an awesome, loving, attentive, playful, Mom to our now 4yo Orli, I‚Äôve tried unpacking with you, being a sounding board, and giving you support  through the difficult time with your funder, and building on the moment last night with your Climber, which you shared back with her....and sharing with you  in the torah study, which I know is important for you, and I‚Äôm enjoying as well. I can do better for you and will make a more concerted effort to verbalize and acknowledge. I am both deeply in awe and in love with you. Your energy for building community....for the Climbers and for us, seems to know no bounds, and I realize that is unfair. Of course you are not superhuman, and tireless. Who is? Sometimes I find it hard to keep up, as your ‚Äúdoing‚Äù in the world moves so quickly, and I just don‚Äôt run as an extrovert in the world.... This tension, that you feel in me as rigidity, which it can be, is also me trying to maintain a sense of order and feel safe, and have boundaries so that I can retain my energy...which comes from the opposite source than for you. I know there is stuff for me to unpack here, as well us for us. I do appreciate all that you do....as mom-in-chief, as our social center of gravity and planner, as a thinker with depth and feeling, as warrior for people of overlooked and hidden talents, as a lover of me, even when I don‚Äôt make it so easy, and our lovely daughter and your step sons, and as a queen, who deserves to be put on a pedestal and honored....because you are one of a kind, selfless, sexy, cherished, and loved....and I will say that over and over and hold you and squeeze until you can barely take a breath. I love you my dear. Nothing, no one in this world (save our children) holds a candle to you. I will work